By Emameh Gabriel. President Muhammadu Buhari will on Thursday present the 2021 appropriation bill to a Joint session of both chambers of the National Assembly. The announcement came following receipt of a letter from the President to the National Assembly last week. The letter was read during the Tuesday plenary by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan. The letter reads: “May I crave the kind indulgence of the Distinguished Senate to grant me the slot of 11:00hrs on Thursday, 8th October, 2020, to formally present the 2021 Appropriation bill to the Joint Session of the National Assembly. “While I look forward to addressing the Joint session, please, accept Mr. Senate President, the assurances of my highest regard.”